results.name: Numbers that occur more than once in A193873, in order of appearance.
comment: Note that a(1) = 1729 is known as the Hardy-Ramanujan number (see A001235).
Apparently these numbers occur only twice in A193873.
Many of these numbers occur more than twice. For example, 812405017 occurs 3 times, a(67), a(134), and a(268). _Robert Price_, Mar 17 2020
link: Robert Price, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2554
formula: This conjecture only holds for n<62: a(62)=A193873(124)=A193873(2n)=620378449
example: 1729 is in the sequence because the Hardy-Ramanujan number is also the smallest product of three distinct primes of the form 3*k+1 and also of the form 6*k+1, so 1729 occurs more than once in A193873.
results.author: _Omar E. Pol_, Sep 02 2011
